Package: parallax
Title: Multi-Platform Point Cloud Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Chris Lyons [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Chris Lyons <chris.lyons@ky.gov>
Authors@R:
    person("Chris", "Lyons", email = "chris.lyons@ky.gov",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Multi-platform point cloud analysis for aerial, terrestrial, and
    UAV LiDAR. Provides registration (ICP, multi-scan alignment), segmentation
    (ground classification, object extraction, tree delineation), surface
    reconstruction (Poisson, ball pivoting, alpha shapes), and geometric feature
    extraction (planes, cylinders, edges). Platform-aware defaults automatically
    adapt processing parameters based on acquisition type. Rust core via
    'extendr' for performance-critical operations.
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
